Subject: CVE-2024-54676: Apache OpenMeetings: Deserialisation of untrusted
 data in cluster mode 

Severity: important

Affected versions:

- Apache OpenMeetings 2.1 before 8.0.0

Description:

Vendor: The Apache Software Foundation

Versions Affected: Apache OpenMeetings from 2.1.0 before 8.0.0

Description: Default clustering instructions at  https://openmeetings.apache.org/Clustering.html Â doesn't specify white/black lists for OpenJPA this leads to possible deserialisation of untrusted data.
Users are recommended to upgrade to version 8.0.0 and update their startup scripts to include the relevant 'openjpa.serialization.class.blacklist' and 'openjpa.serialization.class.whitelist' configurations as shown in the documentation.

This issue is being tracked as OPENMEETINGS-2787 

